## 1. Production EAS submission checklist

The MLabs template ships dev + preview EAS profiles. Production submit is a
per-fork concern — these are the accounts and credentials the client must
own before the app reaches the stores. Reference: [`docs/handover/eas-submission.md`](docs/handover/eas-submission.md).

### iOS

- [ ] **Apple Developer Program** — paid membership ($99/yr, renews annually).
      Account: `{{APPLE_DEVELOPER_ACCOUNT_EMAIL}}`
- [ ] **Apple Team ID** captured: `{{APPLE_TEAM_ID}}`
      Source: Apple Developer Portal → Membership → Team ID.
- [ ] **iOS bundle identifier** assigned: `{{IOS_BUNDLE_ID}}`
      Mirrored in `mobile/app.config.ts` (`ios.bundleIdentifier`).
- [ ] **App Store Connect listing** created (screenshots, description, age
      rating, privacy policy URL, support URL).
- [ ] **App Store Connect API key** generated for EAS Submit
      (Users and Access → Integrations → App Store Connect API).
- [ ] **Associated Domains capability** enabled for the App ID; entry
      added: `applinks:{{PROD_HOST}}`.
- [ ] **TestFlight** internal testers wired (at minimum the client + 1
      MLabs engineer for warranty period).
- [ ] **Push notification entitlement** — deferred for v1 (polling-only).
      When push lands: generate APNs Auth Key, upload via `eas credentials`,
      update `mobile/app.config.ts` ios entitlements.

### Android

- [ ] **Google Play Console** — paid account ($25 one-time).
      Account: `{{GOOGLE_PLAY_ACCOUNT_EMAIL}}`
- [ ] **Android package name** assigned: `{{ANDROID_PACKAGE}}`
      Mirrored in `mobile/app.config.ts` (`android.package`).
- [ ] **Play Console internal track** configured with testers list.
- [ ] **Play Console service account JSON** generated for EAS Submit
      (Setup → API access). Stored at: `{{ANDROID_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_PATH}}`
      (NOT committed; client owns this file).
- [ ] **Signing keys** — Play App Signing enabled (default).
      SHA-256 fingerprint of the **App signing key** (not upload key)
      captured: `{{ANDROID_CERT_SHA256}}`
- [ ] **EAS Submit** profile in `mobile/eas.json` updated with service
      account path.

For step-by-step walkthroughs see [`docs/handover/eas-submission.md`](docs/handover/eas-submission.md).

