## 4. Backups + Disaster recovery

### Neon — Point-in-Time Recovery

Enable PITR on the production Neon project:

```
Neon Console → Project → Settings → Backups → Enable point-in-time recovery
```

Retention: 7 days minimum for paid tier; 24h on free tier. Bump to 30 days
if the client's data-loss tolerance is tighter than a week.

### Recovery commands

To create a recovery branch from a specific moment:

```bash
# Via Neon CLI
neonctl branches create \
  --project-id <project-id> \
  --parent main \
  --name recovery-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M) \
  --parent-timestamp "2026-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ"
```

Then update `DATABASE_URL` to point at the recovery branch's connection
string. Validate, then promote (Neon UI → Branches → recovery → Promote
to main) to make it the new primary.

### Replit Object Storage

Object Storage buckets are append-only in practice (no versioning native).
For DR: client should run a weekly `replit-object-storage cp` mirror to an
external S3 bucket if their data sensitivity warrants it. Out of scope for
v1 — flagged for TODOS.

### Postmark

Postmark retains 45 days of delivery history at the Server level. For
longer audit trails, configure Postmark → Server Settings → Webhooks →
Delivery webhook → POST to client's log sink.

